## Problem

The SearchBar on the homepage (`apps/web/app/[locale]/components/SearchBar.tsx`) requires a mouse click or manual tab navigation to focus. Power users and users who prefer keyboard navigation have no quick way to jump to the search field. Adding a global `/` keyboard shortcut (standard in apps like GitHub, Linear, Notion) would significantly improve usability.

## Files to Touch

- `apps/web/app/[locale]/components/SearchBar.tsx`

## How to Solve

1. Inside the `SearchBar` component, attach a `keydown` event listener on `window` using `useEffect`:
   ```ts
   useEffect(() => {
     const handleKeyDown = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
       if (e.key === "/" && document.activeElement?.tagName !== "INPUT" && document.activeElement?.tagName !== "TEXTAREA") {
         e.preventDefault();
         inputRef.current?.focus();
       }
     };
     window.addEventListener("keydown", handleKeyDown);
     return () => window.removeEventListener("keydown", handleKeyDown);
   }, []);
   ```
2. Make sure the existing `inputRef` in the component is attached to the `<input>` element (check if it already exists, otherwise create it).
3. Add a small `kbd` hint badge inside the search input (right side, like GitHub's `/` key badge) to make the shortcut discoverable.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Pressing `/` anywhere on the homepage focuses the search input.
- [ ] Shortcut does not trigger when user is typing in any other input/textarea.
- [ ] A visual `/` badge hint is visible inside the search bar when unfocused.
- [ ] Pressing `Escape` closes the suggestions dropdown (already implemented — verify it still works).

